module rwmano-project                                                        3
module rwmano-vnfr                                                           4


1  Schema Globals
  Global Schema Type
    rw_ypbc_RwmanoVnfr_t_schema
  Global Schema Pointer
    rw_ypbc_RwmanoVnfr_g_schema
2  module rw-project

2.1  rw-project data
  Description
    This yang module defines project-based tenancy for RIFT.ware.
    Authorization for project access is defined in terms of RIFT.ware's
    Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) model.

2.1.1  list rw-project:project
  Description
    Configuration and state for individual projects.  RIFT.ware
    applications and projects are expected to augment this list in
    order to add configuration for projects that is specific to the
    product or application.  As such, this list contains minimal
    data defined in this yang module.

    When augmenting this element, other yang modules should prefer to
    define containers with the same name as the augmenting module.
    (Augmenting RIFT.ware modules should prefer to augment without
    the rw prefix [for new features], or should prefer to augment the
    augmented container of an existing augment, to ease future
    adoption and/or standardization.)
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the project.
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Information about project
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    C,/rw-project:project
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    C,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    D,/rw-project:project
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    D,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']
  Protobuf Type
    .rwmano_vnfr.YangData.RwProject.Project
  Python Proto-GI Type
    RwmanoVnfrYang.YangData_RwProject_Project
  C Protobuf-C Struct Type
    RwmanoVnfr__YangData__RwProject__Project
  C RWPB Identifiers
    RwmanoVnfr_RwProject_data_Project
  YPBC Base Identifier
    rw_ypbc_RwmanoVnfr_RwProject_data_Project

2.1.1.1.1  list rw-project:user
  Description
    The list of Users who have been assigned Roles within this
    Project.
  Leaves
    name: user-domain, type: LEAFREF, description: The user domain.  This is the source of the user identity.
    Different domains may duplicate a user-name, but such users
    would be considered distinct by RIFT.ware.
    name: user-name, type: LEAFREF, description: The user name.  The syntax of this name depends on the domain.
    For example, if the domain is a login name, it might be limited
    to alphanumeric characters.  However, if the domain is email address,
    the syntax could include additional characters, such as the at(@) sign.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rw-project:project-config/rw-project:user
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rw-project:project-config/rw-project:user[rw-project:user-name='STRING'][rw-project:user-domain='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/project-config/user/STRING,STRING
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    C,/rw-project:project/rw-project:project-config/rw-project:user
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    C,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rw-project:project-config/rw-project:user[rw-project:user-name='STRING'][rw-project:user-domain='STRING']

    .rw_project.YangData.RwProject.Project.ProjectConfig.User

    RwProjectYang.YangData_RwProject_Project_ProjectConfig_User

    RwProject__YangData__RwProject__Project__ProjectConfig__User
  C RWPB Identifiers

  YPBC Base Identifier

    For example, if the domain is a login name, it might be limited
    to alphanumeric characters.  However, if the domain is some
    kind of email address, the syntax could include assitional
    characters, such as the at sign.

  Description
    The state of the Roles the User has been assigned.
  Leaves
    name: role, type: STRING, description: The Role, independent of Keys.
    name: state, type: STRING, description: The assignment of a User to a Role may be an asynchronous
    operation.  This value indicates whether the Role
    assignment is active.  If the value is 'active', then the
    assignment is complete and active.  Any other value
    indicates that Role assignment is in a transitional or
    failed state, as described in the value.

2.1.1.3.1.1  list rwmanovlr:vlr
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the VLR.
    name: name, type: STRING, description: VLR name.
    name: nsr-id-ref, type: STRING, description: NS instance identifier.
    This is a leafref /rwmanoproject:project/internal/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr/nsr:id
    name: vld-ref, type: STRING, description: Reference to VLD
    /rwmanoproject:project/internal/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr[nsr:id=../nsr-id-ref]
    /nsd/vld:vld/vld:id
    name: res-id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for resmgr id mapping
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: vendor, type: STRING, description: Provider of the VLR.
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description of the VLR.
    name: version, type: STRING, description: Version of the VLR
    name: type, type: ENUM
    name: root-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the aggregate bandwidth.
    name: leaf-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the bandwidth of branches.
    name: create-time, type: UINT32, description: Creation timestamp of this Virtual Link.
    The timestamp is expressed as seconds
    since unix epoch - 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z
    name: mgmt-network, type: BOOLEAN, description: Is this a management network?
    name: network-id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the allocated network resource.
    name: vim-network-name, type: STRING, description: Name of network in VIM account. This is used to indicate
    pre-provisioned network name in cloud account.
    name: status, type: ENUM, description: Status of the virtual link record.
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of the Virtual Link
    init                 : The VL is in init stat.
    vl-alloc-pending     : The VL alloc is pending in VIM
    running              : The VL is up  and running in VM
    vl-terminate-pending : The VL is being terminated in VIM.
    terminated           : The VL is terminated in the VM.
    failed               : The VL instantiation failed in VIM.

    name: datacenter, type: STRING, description: Datacenter name to use when instantiating
    the network service.
    name: network-pool, type: STRING, description: The network pool the resource was allocated from.
    name: ipv4-nat-pool-name, type: STRING, description: IPV4 nat pool name
    name: operational-status-details, type: STRING, description: The error message in case of a failed VLR operational status
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovlr:vlr-catalog/rwmanovlr:vlr
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovlr:vlr-catalog/rwmanovlr:vlr[rwmanovlr:id='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-vlr:vlr-catalog/vlr/STRING
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    D,/rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovlr:vlr-catalog/rwmanovlr:vlr
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    D,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovlr:vlr-catalog/rwmanovlr:vlr[rwmanovlr:id='STRING']

  Leaves

    network is built.
    name: overlay-type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the overlay network.
    LOCAL - Provider network implemented in a single compute node
    FLAT - Provider network shared by all tenants
    VLAN - Provider network implemented using 802.1Q tagging
    VXLAN - Provider networks implemented using RFC 7348
    GRE - Provider networks implemented using GRE tunnels

2.1.1.3.2.1.2.1  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:rule
  Description
    List of rules needed for security groups
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Name/id of the rule
    name: direction, type: ENUM, description: Direction of traffic w.r.t VDU
    name: ethertype, type: ENUM, description: IPv4 or IPv6
    name: ip-protocol, type: UINT8, description: IP protocol, 0-255
    name: ip-protocol-string, type: ENUM, description: IP protocol string, within the following values
    any or 0, ah or 51, dccp or 33, egp or 8, esp or 50, gre or 47, icmp or 1, icmpv6 or 58,
    igmp or 2, ipip or 4, ipv6-encap or 41, ipv6-frag or 44, ipv6-icmp or 58, ipv6-nonxt or 59,
    ipv6-opts or 60, ipv6-route or 43, ospf or 89, pgm or 113, rsvp or 46, sctp or 132, tcp or 6,
    udp or 17, udplite or 136, vrrp or 112. 
    name: port-range-min, type: UINT16, description: Minimum port number in the range 0-65535
    name: port-range-max, type: UINT16, description: Maximum port number in the range 0-65535
    name: cidr, type: UNION, description: Known CIDR
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:security-group/rwmanoprojectvnfd:rule

2.1.1.3.2.1.3.1  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:config-parameter-source
  Description
    The list of parameters exposed by this VNF
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the source
    name: description, type: STRING, description:  Description of the source
    name: descriptor, type: STRING, description: Location of this source as an xpath.
    For example:
    ../../../mgmt-interface/port
    name: attribute, type: STRING, description: Location of this source as runtime attribute.
    The value is <xpath>, <attribute_name>
    For example:
    ../../../mgmt-interface, ip-address
    which retruns the ip-address assigned to the
    mgmt-interface after VNF instantiation.
    name: config-primitive-name-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: A leafref to configuration primitive.
    This refers to a config parameter whose
    output parameter is referred in out-parameter.
    name: parameter-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Name of the output parameter in the config primitiive
    name: value, type: STRING, description: Pre-defined value to be used for this source
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:config-parameter/rwmanoprojectvnfd:config-parameter-source

2.1.1.3.2.1.7  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:connection-point
  Description
    List for external connection points. Each VNF has one
    or more external connection points that connect the VNF
    to other VNFs or to external networks. Each VNF exposes
    connection points to the orchestrator, which can construct
    network services by connecting the connection points
    between different VNFs. The NFVO will use VLDs and VNFFGs
    at the network service level to construct network services.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the connection point
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the internal connection points
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
    name: port-security-enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Enables the port security for the port
    name: vlr-ref, type: STRING, description: Reference to VLR id
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:connection-point

2.1.1.3.2.1.8.2  container rwmanoprojectvnfd:guest-epa
  Leaves
    name: trusted-execution, type: BOOLEAN, description: This VM should be allocated from trusted pool
    name: mempage-size, type: ENUM, description: Memory page allocation size. If a VM requires
    hugepages, it should choose LARGE or SIZE_2MB
    or SIZE_1GB. If the VM prefers hugepages it
    should choose PREFER_LARGE.
    LARGE        : Require hugepages (either 2MB or 1GB)
    SMALL        : Doesn't require hugepages
    SIZE_2MB     : Requires 2MB hugepages
    SIZE_1GB     : Requires 1GB hugepages
    PREFER_LARGE : Application prefers hugepages
    name: cpu-pinning-policy, type: ENUM, description: CPU pinning policy describes association
    between virtual CPUs in guest and the
    physical CPUs in the host.
    DEDICATED : Virtual CPUs are pinned to
      physical CPUs
    SHARED    : Multiple VMs may share the
      same physical CPUs.
    ANY       : Any policy is acceptable for the VM
    name: cpu-thread-pinning-policy, type: ENUM, description: CPU thread pinning policy describes how to
    place the guest CPUs when the host supports
    hyper threads:
    AVOID   : Avoids placing a guest on a host
    with threads.
    SEPARATE: Places vCPUs on separate cores,
    and avoids placing two vCPUs on
    two threads of same core.
    ISOLATE : Places each vCPU on a different core,
    and places no vCPUs from a different
    guest on the same core.
    PREFER  : Attempts to place vCPUs on threads
    of the same core.
    name: numa-unaware, type: EMPTY
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vdu/rwmanoprojectvnfd:guest-epa
  XPath Keyed Path

2.1.1.3.2.1.8.2.2  container rwmanoprojectvnfd:numa-node-policy
  Description
    This policy defines NUMA topology of the
    guest. Specifically identifies if the guest
    should be run on a host with one NUMA
    node or multiple NUMA nodes. As an example
    a guest might need 8 VCPUs and 4 GB of
    memory. However, it might need the VCPUs
    and memory distributed across multiple
    NUMA nodes. In this scenario, NUMA node
    1 could run with 6 VCPUs and 3GB, and
    NUMA node 2 could run with 2 VCPUs and
    1GB.
  Leaves
    name: node-cnt, type: UINT16, description: The number of NUMA nodes to expose to the VM.
    name: mem-policy, type: ENUM, description: This policy specifies how the memory should
    be allocated in a multi-node scenario.
    STRICT    : The memory must be allocated
    strictly from the memory attached
    to the NUMA node.

2.1.1.3.2.1.8.6  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:alarm
  Leaves
    name: alarm-id, type: STRING, description: This field is reserved for the identifier assigned by the VIM provider
    name: name, type: STRING, description: A human readable string to identify the alarm
    name: description, type: STRING, description: A description of this alarm
    name: vdur-id, type: STRING, description: The identifier of the VDUR that the alarm is associated with
    name: repeat, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates whether the alarm should be repeatedly emitted
    while the associated threshold has been crossed.
    name: enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates whether the alarm has been enabled or
    disabled.
    name: severity, type: ENUM, description: A measure of the importance or urgency of the alarm
    name: metric, type: ENUM, description: The metric to be tracked by this alarm.
    name: statistic, type: ENUM, description: The type of metric statistic that is tracked by this alarm
    name: operation, type: ENUM, description: The relational operator used to define whether an alarm should be
    triggered in certain scenarios, such as if the metric statistic
    goes above or below a specified value.
    name: value, type: DECIMAL64, description: This value defines the threshold that, if crossed, will trigger
    the alarm.
    name: period, type: UINT32, description: The period defines the length of time (seconds) that the metric
    data are collected over in oreder to evaluate the chosen
    statistic.
    name: evaluations, type: UINT32, description: Defines the length of time (seconds) in which metric data are
    collected in order to evaluate the chosen statistic.

2.1.1.3.2.1.8.8  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:internal-connection-point
  Description
    List for internal connection points. Each VNFC
    has zero or more internal connection points.
    Internal connection points are used for connecting
    the VNF with components internal to the VNF. If a VNF
    has only one VNFC, it may not have any internal
    connection points.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the connection point
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the internal connection points
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
    name: port-security-enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Enables the port security for the port
    name: vlr-ref, type: STRING, description: Reference to VLR id
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vdu/rwmanoprojectvnfd:internal-connection-point
  XPath Keyed Path

2.1.1.3.2.1.8.9.2  container rwmanoprojectvnfd:virtual-interface
  Description
    Container for the virtual interface properties
  Leaves
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Specifies the type of virtual interface
    between VM and host.
    VIRTIO          : Use the traditional VIRTIO interface.
    PCI-PASSTHROUGH : Use PCI-PASSTHROUGH interface.
    SR-IOV          : Use SR-IOV interface.
    SRIOV-DIRECT-PHYSICAL: Use SR-IOV interface with direct-physical.
    E1000           : Emulate E1000 interface.
    RTL8139         : Emulate RTL8139 interface.
    PCNET           : Emulate PCNET interface.
    AVP             : Windriver Accelerated Virtual port
    OM-MGMT         : Used to specify openmano mgmt external-connection type
    name: vpci, type: STRING, description: Specifies the virtual PCI address. Expressed in
    the following format dddd:dd:dd.d. For example
    0000:00:12.0. This information can be used to
    pass as metadata during the VM creation.
    name: bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: Aggregate bandwidth of the NIC.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vdu/rwmanoprojectvnfd:interface/rwmanoprojectvnfd:virtual-interface

2.1.1.3.2.1.8.10  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:volumes
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name for the volume configuration
    name: device-name, type: STRING, description: Device-name of the disk eg. vda, vdb etc
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description for Volume
    name: size, type: UINT64, description: Size of disk in GB
    name: ephemeral, type: EMPTY
    name: image, type: STRING, description: Image name for the software image.
    If the image name is found within the VNF package it will
    be uploaded to all VIM accounts during onboarding process.
    Otherwise, the image must be added to the VIM account with
    the same name as entered here.

    name: image-checksum, type: STRING, description: Image md5sum for the software image.
    The md5sum, if provided, along with the image name uniquely
    identifies an image uploaded to the CAL.

    name: volume-ref, type: STRING, description: A reference to or the name of a pre-existing volume in the VIM
    name: boot-volume, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates if this is boot volume or not
    name: boot-priority, type: INT32, description: Boot priority associated with volume
    name: device-bus, type: ENUM, description: Type of disk-bus on which this disk is exposed to guest
    name: device-type, type: ENUM, description: The type of device as exposed to guest

2.1.1.3.2.1.10  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:http-endpoint
  Description
    List of http endpoints to be used by monitoring params
  Leaves
    name: path, type: STRING, description: The HTTP path on the management server
    name: https, type: BOOLEAN, description: Pick HTTPS instead of HTTP , Default is false
    name: port, type: UINT16, description: The HTTP port to connect to
    name: username, type: STRING, description: The HTTP basic auth username
    name: password, type: STRING, description: The HTTP basic auth password
    name: polling-interval-secs, type: UINT8, description: The HTTP polling interval in seconds
    name: method, type: ENUM, description: Method that the URI should perform.
    Deafult action is GET.
    name: data, type: STRING, description: This is the data to be sent with POST 
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.2.1.12  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:placement-groups
  Description
    List of placement groups at VNF level
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Place group construct to define the compute resource placement strategy
    in cloud environment
    name: requirement, type: STRING, description: This is free text space used to describe the intent/rationale
    behind this placement group. This is for human consumption only
    name: strategy, type: ENUM, description: Strategy associated with this placement group
    Following values are possible
      - COLOCATION: Colocation strategy imply intent to share the physical
                    infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among all members
                    of this group.
      - ISOLATION: Isolation strategy imply intent to not share the physical
                   infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among the members
                   of this group.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:placement-groups

2.1.1.3.2.1.13  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:tca-policy
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Policy ID
    name: operator, type: ENUM, description: How to compare each sample with the threshold to determine if
    the threshold has been crossed.
    name: hold-on-for-n-samples, type: UINT32, description: The number of samples for which the condition (sample value <operator>
    threshold) is met in order to raise an alarm or upgrade the severity
    of the Threshold Crossing Alarm.
    name: hold-off-for-n-samples, type: UINT32, description: The number of samples for which the condition ( sample value
    <operator> threshold) is NOT be met in order to clear an alarm
    or downgrade the severity of the Threshold Crossing Alarm.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:tca-policy

2.1.1.3.2.1.13.1  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:threshold
  Description
    When enough sample values are found to be above/below(depending
    on defined operator) the defined threshold a Threshold Crossing
    Alert(TCA) alarm is generated. When enough samples are found to
    be crossing the threshold in the reverse direction will either
    clear the alarm or downgrade its severity
  Leaves
    name: severity, type: ENUM, description: The severity of the alarm generated when the threshold is crossed.
    If using operator=GT, threshold values must comply with this constraint:
    minor < major < critical. If using operator=LT, threshold values
    must comply with this constraint: minor > major > critical.
    name: value, type: DECIMAL64, description: Threshold value
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectvnfd:threshold
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd[rwmanoprojectvnfd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectvnfd:tca-policy[rwmanoprojectvnfd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectvnfd:threshold[rwmanoprojectvnfd:severity='MINOR']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-project-vnfd:vnfd-catalog/vnfd/STRING/tca-policy/STRING/threshold/MINOR
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    C,/rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectvnfd:threshold
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    C,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd[rwmanoprojectvnfd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectvnfd:tca-policy[rwmanoprojectvnfd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectvnfd:threshold[rwmanoprojectvnfd:severity='MINOR']
  Protobuf Type
    .rwmano_project_vnfd.YangData.RwProject.Project.Internal.VnfdCatalog.Vnfd.TcaPolicy.Threshold

    RwmanoProjectVnfdYang.YangData_RwProject_Project_Internal_VnfdCatalog_Vnfd_TcaPolicy_Threshold

2.1.1.3.2.1.13.1.1  list rwmanoprojectvnfd:action
  Description
    Actions to take when the threshold is crossed.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of action
    name: threshold-adjustment, type: DECIMAL64, description: Amount by which all thresholds defined are to be adjusted when
    this action is taken. Typical use case is for scale-in/scale-out.
    If scale-out is based on number of sessions, the first scale-out
    occurs at a certain threshold but the second scale-out will occur
    at a much higher session count than the first since now more resources
    are allocated allowing for more sessions.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectvnfd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectvnfd:threshold/rwmanoprojectvnfd:action
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd-catalog/rwmanoprojectvnfd:vnfd[rwmanoprojectvnfd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectvnfd:tca-policy[rwmanoprojectvnfd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectvnfd:threshold[rwmanoprojectvnfd:severity='MINOR']/rwmanoprojectvnfd:action[rwmanoprojectvnfd:name='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-project-vnfd:vnfd-catalog/vnfd/STRING/tca-policy/STRING/threshold/MINOR/action/STRING
  RW Keyspec XPath Path

    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description of the NSD.
    name: version, type: STRING, description: Version of the NSD

2.1.1.3.3.1.1  list rwmanoprojectnsd:connection-point
  Description
    List for external connection points.
    Each NS has one or more external connection
    points. As the name implies that external
    connection points are used for connecting
    the NS to other NS or to external networks.
    Each NS exposes these connection points to
    the orchestrator. The orchestrator can
    construct network service chains by
    connecting the connection points between
    different NS.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the NS connection point.
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:connection-point

2.1.1.3.3.1.2  list rwmanoprojectnsd:scaling-group-descriptor
  Description
    scaling group descriptor within this network service.
    The scaling group defines a group of VNFs,
    and the ratio of VNFs in the network service
    that is used as target for scaling action
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of this scaling group.
    name: min-instance-count, type: UINT32, description: Minimum instances of the scaling group which are allowed.
    These instances are created by default when the network service
    is instantiated.
    name: max-instance-count, type: UINT32, description: Maximum instances of this scaling group that are allowed
    in a single network service. The network service scaling
    will fail, when the number of service group instances
    exceed the max-instance-count specified.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:scaling-group-descriptor

2.1.1.3.3.1.2.1  list rwmanoprojectnsd:scaling-policy
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the scaling policy
    name: scaling-type, type: ENUM, description: Type of scaling
    name: enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Specifies if the scaling policy can be applied
    name: scale-in-operation-type, type: ENUM, description: Operation to be applied to check between scaling criterias to
    check if the scale in threshold condition has been met.
    Defaults to AND
    name: scale-out-operation-type, type: ENUM, description: Operation to be applied to check between scaling criterias to
    check if the scale out threshold condition has been met.
    Defauls to OR
    name: threshold-time, type: UINT32, description: The duration for which the criteria must hold true
    name: cooldown-time, type: UINT32, description: The duration after a scaling-in/scaling-out action has been
    triggered, for which there will be no further optional

2.1.1.3.3.1.2.4  list rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Policy ID
    name: operator, type: ENUM, description: How to compare each sample with the threshold to determine if
    the threshold has been crossed.
    name: hold-on-for-n-samples, type: UINT32, description: The number of samples for which the condition (sample value <operator>
    threshold) is met in order to raise an alarm or upgrade the severity
    of the Threshold Crossing Alarm.
    name: hold-off-for-n-samples, type: UINT32, description: The number of samples for which the condition ( sample value
    <operator> threshold) is NOT be met in order to clear an alarm
    or downgrade the severity of the Threshold Crossing Alarm.
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.3.1.2.4.1  list rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold
  Description
    When enough sample values are found to be above/below(depending
    on defined operator) the defined threshold a Threshold Crossing
    Alert(TCA) alarm is generated. When enough samples are found to
    be crossing the threshold in the reverse direction will either
    clear the alarm or downgrade its severity
  Leaves
    name: severity, type: ENUM, description: The severity of the alarm generated when the threshold is crossed.
    If using operator=GT, threshold values must comply with this constraint:
    minor < major < critical. If using operator=LT, threshold values
    must comply with this constraint: minor > major > critical.
    name: value, type: DECIMAL64, description: Threshold value
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:scaling-group-descriptor/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:scaling-group-descriptor[rwmanoprojectnsd:name='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold[rwmanoprojectnsd:severity='MINOR']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-project-nsd:nsd-catalog/nsd/STRING/scaling-group-descriptor/STRING/tca-policy/STRING/threshold/MINOR
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    C,/rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:scaling-group-descriptor/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    C,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:scaling-group-descriptor[rwmanoprojectnsd:name='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold[rwmanoprojectnsd:severity='MINOR']

2.1.1.3.3.1.2.4.1.1  list rwmanoprojectnsd:action
  Description
    Actions to take when the threshold is crossed.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of action
    name: threshold-adjustment, type: DECIMAL64, description: Amount by which all thresholds defined are to be adjusted when
    this action is taken. Typical use case is for scale-in/scale-out.
    If scale-out is based on number of sessions, the first scale-out
    occurs at a certain threshold but the second scale-out will occur
    at a much higher session count than the first since now more resources
    are allocated allowing for more sessions.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:scaling-group-descriptor/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold/rwmanoprojectnsd:action
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:scaling-group-descriptor[rwmanoprojectnsd:name='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold[rwmanoprojectnsd:severity='MINOR']/rwmanoprojectnsd:action[rwmanoprojectnsd:name='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-project-nsd:nsd-catalog/nsd/STRING/scaling-group-descriptor/STRING/tca-policy/STRING/threshold/MINOR/action/STRING
  RW Keyspec XPath Path

  Description

  Leaves
    name: member-vnf-index-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Reference to member-vnf within constituent-vnfds
    name: order, type: UINT8, description: A number that denotes the order of a VNF in a chain
    name: vnfd-id-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: A reference to a vnfd. This is a
    leafref to path:
        ../../../../nsd:constituent-vnfd
        + [nsd:id = current()/../nsd:id-ref]
        + /nsd:vnfd-id-ref
    name: vnfd-connection-point-ref, type: STRING, description: A reference to a connection point name
    in a vnfd. This is a leafref to path:
        /vnfd:vnfd-catalog/vnfd:vnfd
        + [vnfd:id = current()/../nsd:vnfd-id-ref]
        + /vnfd:connection-point/vnfd:name

    use of xpath. Seems to be an issue with leafref
    to leafref, whose target is in a different module.
    Once that is resolved this will switched to use
    leafref

    name: vendor, type: STRING, description: Provider of the VLD.
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description of the VLD.
    name: version, type: STRING, description: Version of the VLD
    name: type, type: ENUM
    name: root-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the aggregate bandwidth.
    name: leaf-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the bandwidth of branches.
    name: mgmt-network, type: BOOLEAN, description: Flag indicating whether this network is a VIM management network
    name: vim-network-name, type: STRING, description: Name of network in VIM account. This is used to indicate
    pre-provisioned network name in cloud account.
    name: ip-profile-ref, type: STRING, description: Named reference to IP-profile object
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.3.1.11.2  container rwmanoprojectnsd:provider-network
  Description
    Container for the provider network.
  Leaves
    name: physical-network, type: STRING, description: Name of the physical network on which the provider
    network is built.
    name: overlay-type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the overlay network.
    LOCAL - Provider network implemented in a single compute node
    FLAT - Provider network shared by all tenants
    VLAN - Provider network implemented using 802.1Q tagging
    VXLAN - Provider networks implemented using RFC 7348
    GRE - Provider networks implemented using GRE tunnels
    name: segmentation_id, type: UINT32, description: ID of segregated virtual networks
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.2.1  list rwmanoprojectnsd:rule
  Description
    List of rules needed for security groups
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Name/id of the rule
    name: direction, type: ENUM, description: Direction of traffic w.r.t VDU
    name: ethertype, type: ENUM, description: IPv4 or IPv6
    name: ip-protocol, type: UINT8, description: IP protocol, 0-255
    name: ip-protocol-string, type: ENUM, description: IP protocol string, within the following values
    any or 0, ah or 51, dccp or 33, egp or 8, esp or 50, gre or 47, icmp or 1, icmpv6 or 58,
    igmp or 2, ipip or 4, ipv6-encap or 41, ipv6-frag or 44, ipv6-icmp or 58, ipv6-nonxt or 59,
    ipv6-opts or 60, ipv6-route or 43, ospf or 89, pgm or 113, rsvp or 46, sctp or 132, tcp or 6,
    udp or 17, udplite or 136, vrrp or 112. 
    name: port-range-min, type: UINT16, description: Minimum port number in the range 0-65535
    name: port-range-max, type: UINT16, description: Maximum port number in the range 0-65535
    name: cidr, type: UNION, description: Known CIDR
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.3.1  list rwmanoprojectnsd:config-parameter-source
  Description
    The list of parameters exposed by this VNF
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the source
    name: description, type: STRING, description:  Description of the source
    name: descriptor, type: STRING, description: Location of this source as an xpath.
    For example:
    ../../../mgmt-interface/port
    name: attribute, type: STRING, description: Location of this source as runtime attribute.
    The value is <xpath>, <attribute_name>
    For example:
    ../../../mgmt-interface, ip-address
    which retruns the ip-address assigned to the
    mgmt-interface after VNF instantiation.
    name: config-primitive-name-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: A leafref to configuration primitive.
    This refers to a config parameter whose
    output parameter is referred in out-parameter.
    name: parameter-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Name of the output parameter in the config primitiive
    name: value, type: STRING, description: Pre-defined value to be used for this source
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.5  list rwmanoprojectnsd:internal-vld
  Description
    List of Internal Virtual Link Descriptors (VLD).
    The internal VLD describes the basic topology of
    the connectivity such as E-LAN, E-Line, E-Tree.
    between internal VNF components of the system.
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the VLD
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the internal VLD
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: description, type: STRING
    name: type, type: ENUM
    name: resource-name, type: STRING, description: Internal VL name in VIM
    name: root-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the aggregate bandwidth.
    name: leaf-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the bandwidth of branches.
    name: vim-network-name, type: STRING, description: Name of network in VIM account. This is used to indicate
    pre-provisioned network name in cloud account.
    name: ip-profile-ref, type: STRING, description: Named reference to IP-profile object
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:constituent-vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:internal-vld

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.7  list rwmanoprojectnsd:connection-point
  Description
    List for external connection points. Each VNF has one
    or more external connection points that connect the VNF
    to other VNFs or to external networks. Each VNF exposes
    connection points to the orchestrator, which can construct
    network services by connecting the connection points
    between different VNFs. The NFVO will use VLDs and VNFFGs
    at the network service level to construct network services.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the connection point
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the internal connection points
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
    name: port-security-enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Enables the port security for the port
    name: vlr-ref, type: STRING, description: Reference to VLR id
  XPath Path

    pass as metadata during the VM creation.

    If the image name is found within the VNF package it will
    be uploaded to all VIM accounts during onboarding process.
    Otherwise, the image must be added to the VIM account with
    the same name as entered here.

    name: image-checksum, type: STRING, description: Image md5sum for the software image.
    The md5sum, if provided, along with the image name uniquely
    identifies an image uploaded to the CAL.

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.8.2  container rwmanoprojectnsd:guest-epa
  Leaves
    name: trusted-execution, type: BOOLEAN, description: This VM should be allocated from trusted pool
    name: mempage-size, type: ENUM, description: Memory page allocation size. If a VM requires
    hugepages, it should choose LARGE or SIZE_2MB
    or SIZE_1GB. If the VM prefers hugepages it
    should choose PREFER_LARGE.
    LARGE        : Require hugepages (either 2MB or 1GB)
    SMALL        : Doesn't require hugepages
    SIZE_2MB     : Requires 2MB hugepages
    SIZE_1GB     : Requires 1GB hugepages
    PREFER_LARGE : Application prefers hugepages
    name: cpu-pinning-policy, type: ENUM, description: CPU pinning policy describes association
    between virtual CPUs in guest and the
    physical CPUs in the host.
    DEDICATED : Virtual CPUs are pinned to
      physical CPUs
    SHARED    : Multiple VMs may share the
      same physical CPUs.
    ANY       : Any policy is acceptable for the VM
    name: cpu-thread-pinning-policy, type: ENUM, description: CPU thread pinning policy describes how to
    place the guest CPUs when the host supports
    hyper threads:
    AVOID   : Avoids placing a guest on a host
    with threads.
    SEPARATE: Places vCPUs on separate cores,
    and avoids placing two vCPUs on
    two threads of same core.
    ISOLATE : Places each vCPU on a different core,
    and places no vCPUs from a different
    guest on the same core.
    PREFER  : Attempts to place vCPUs on threads
    of the same core.
    name: numa-unaware, type: EMPTY
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:constituent-vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vdu/rwmanoprojectnsd:guest-epa
  XPath Keyed Path

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.8.2.2  container rwmanoprojectnsd:numa-node-policy
  Description
    This policy defines NUMA topology of the
    guest. Specifically identifies if the guest
    should be run on a host with one NUMA
    node or multiple NUMA nodes. As an example
    a guest might need 8 VCPUs and 4 GB of
    memory. However, it might need the VCPUs
    and memory distributed across multiple
    NUMA nodes. In this scenario, NUMA node
    1 could run with 6 VCPUs and 3GB, and
    NUMA node 2 could run with 2 VCPUs and
    1GB.
  Leaves
    name: node-cnt, type: UINT16, description: The number of NUMA nodes to expose to the VM.
    name: mem-policy, type: ENUM, description: This policy specifies how the memory should
    be allocated in a multi-node scenario.
    STRICT    : The memory must be allocated
    strictly from the memory attached
    to the NUMA node.
    PREFERRED : The memory should be allocated
    preferentially from the memory
    attached to the NUMA node
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:constituent-vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vdu/rwmanoprojectnsd:guest-epa/rwmanoprojectnsd:numa-node-policy
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:constituent-vnfd[rwmanoprojectnsd:member-vnf-index='0']/rwmanoprojectnsd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vdu[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:guest-epa/rwmanoprojectnsd:numa-node-policy
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-project-nsd:nsd-catalog/nsd/STRING/constituent-vnfd/0/vnfd/vdu/STRING/guest-epa/numa-node-policy

    name: name, type: STRING, description: A human readable string to identify the alarm
    name: description, type: STRING, description: A description of this alarm
    name: vdur-id, type: STRING, description: The identifier of the VDUR that the alarm is associated with
    name: repeat, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates whether the alarm should be repeatedly emitted
    while the associated threshold has been crossed.
    name: enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates whether the alarm has been enabled or
    disabled.
    name: severity, type: ENUM, description: A measure of the importance or urgency of the alarm
    name: metric, type: ENUM, description: The metric to be tracked by this alarm.
    name: statistic, type: ENUM, description: The type of metric statistic that is tracked by this alarm
    name: operation, type: ENUM, description: The relational operator used to define whether an alarm should be
    triggered in certain scenarios, such as if the metric statistic
    goes above or below a specified value.
    name: value, type: DECIMAL64, description: This value defines the threshold that, if crossed, will trigger
    the alarm.
    name: period, type: UINT32, description: The period defines the length of time (seconds) that the metric
    data are collected over in oreder to evaluate the chosen
    statistic.
    name: evaluations, type: UINT32, description: Defines the length of time (seconds) in which metric data are
    collected in order to evaluate the chosen statistic.

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.8.8  list rwmanoprojectnsd:internal-connection-point
  Description
    List for internal connection points. Each VNFC
    has zero or more internal connection points.
    Internal connection points are used for connecting
    the VNF with components internal to the VNF. If a VNF
    has only one VNFC, it may not have any internal
    connection points.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the connection point
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the internal connection points
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
    name: port-security-enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Enables the port security for the port
    name: vlr-ref, type: STRING, description: Reference to VLR id
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:constituent-vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vdu/rwmanoprojectnsd:internal-connection-point

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.8.9.2  container rwmanoprojectnsd:virtual-interface
  Description
    Container for the virtual interface properties
  Leaves
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Specifies the type of virtual interface
    between VM and host.
    VIRTIO          : Use the traditional VIRTIO interface.
    PCI-PASSTHROUGH : Use PCI-PASSTHROUGH interface.
    SR-IOV          : Use SR-IOV interface.
    SRIOV-DIRECT-PHYSICAL: Use SR-IOV interface with direct-physical.
    E1000           : Emulate E1000 interface.
    RTL8139         : Emulate RTL8139 interface.
    PCNET           : Emulate PCNET interface.
    AVP             : Windriver Accelerated Virtual port
    OM-MGMT         : Used to specify openmano mgmt external-connection type
    name: vpci, type: STRING, description: Specifies the virtual PCI address. Expressed in
    the following format dddd:dd:dd.d. For example
    0000:00:12.0. This information can be used to
    pass as metadata during the VM creation.
    name: bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: Aggregate bandwidth of the NIC.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:constituent-vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vdu/rwmanoprojectnsd:interface/rwmanoprojectnsd:virtual-interface

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.8.10  list rwmanoprojectnsd:volumes
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name for the volume configuration
    name: device-name, type: STRING, description: Device-name of the disk eg. vda, vdb etc
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description for Volume
    name: size, type: UINT64, description: Size of disk in GB
    name: ephemeral, type: EMPTY
    name: image, type: STRING, description: Image name for the software image.
    If the image name is found within the VNF package it will
    be uploaded to all VIM accounts during onboarding process.
    Otherwise, the image must be added to the VIM account with
    the same name as entered here.

    name: image-checksum, type: STRING, description: Image md5sum for the software image.
    The md5sum, if provided, along with the image name uniquely
    identifies an image uploaded to the CAL.

    name: volume-ref, type: STRING, description: A reference to or the name of a pre-existing volume in the VIM
    name: boot-volume, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates if this is boot volume or not
    name: boot-priority, type: INT32, description: Boot priority associated with volume
    name: device-bus, type: ENUM, description: Type of disk-bus on which this disk is exposed to guest
    name: device-type, type: ENUM, description: The type of device as exposed to guest
    name: volume-type, type: STRING, description: Type of the volume
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:constituent-vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vdu/rwmanoprojectnsd:volumes

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.12  list rwmanoprojectnsd:placement-groups
  Description
    List of placement groups at VNF level
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Place group construct to define the compute resource placement strategy
    in cloud environment
    name: requirement, type: STRING, description: This is free text space used to describe the intent/rationale
    behind this placement group. This is for human consumption only
    name: strategy, type: ENUM, description: Strategy associated with this placement group
    Following values are possible
      - COLOCATION: Colocation strategy imply intent to share the physical
                    infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among all members
                    of this group.
      - ISOLATION: Isolation strategy imply intent to not share the physical
                   infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among the members
                   of this group.
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.13  list rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Policy ID
    name: operator, type: ENUM, description: How to compare each sample with the threshold to determine if
    the threshold has been crossed.
    name: hold-on-for-n-samples, type: UINT32, description: The number of samples for which the condition (sample value <operator>
    threshold) is met in order to raise an alarm or upgrade the severity
    of the Threshold Crossing Alarm.
    name: hold-off-for-n-samples, type: UINT32, description: The number of samples for which the condition ( sample value
    <operator> threshold) is NOT be met in order to clear an alarm
    or downgrade the severity of the Threshold Crossing Alarm.
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.13.1  list rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold
  Description
    When enough sample values are found to be above/below(depending
    on defined operator) the defined threshold a Threshold Crossing
    Alert(TCA) alarm is generated. When enough samples are found to
    be crossing the threshold in the reverse direction will either
    clear the alarm or downgrade its severity
  Leaves
    name: severity, type: ENUM, description: The severity of the alarm generated when the threshold is crossed.
    If using operator=GT, threshold values must comply with this constraint:
    minor < major < critical. If using operator=LT, threshold values
    must comply with this constraint: minor > major > critical.
    name: value, type: DECIMAL64, description: Threshold value
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:constituent-vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:constituent-vnfd[rwmanoprojectnsd:member-vnf-index='0']/rwmanoprojectnsd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold[rwmanoprojectnsd:severity='MINOR']

2.1.1.3.3.1.12.1.13.1.1  list rwmanoprojectnsd:action
  Description
    Actions to take when the threshold is crossed.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of action
    name: threshold-adjustment, type: DECIMAL64, description: Amount by which all thresholds defined are to be adjusted when
    this action is taken. Typical use case is for scale-in/scale-out.
    If scale-out is based on number of sessions, the first scale-out
    occurs at a certain threshold but the second scale-out will occur
    at a much higher session count than the first since now more resources
    are allocated allowing for more sessions.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:constituent-vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:vnfd/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold/rwmanoprojectnsd:action

2.1.1.3.3.1.13  list rwmanoprojectnsd:placement-groups
  Description
    List of placement groups at NS level
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Place group construct to define the compute resource placement strategy
    in cloud environment
    name: requirement, type: STRING, description: This is free text space used to describe the intent/rationale
    behind this placement group. This is for human consumption only
    name: strategy, type: ENUM, description: Strategy associated with this placement group
    Following values are possible
      - COLOCATION: Colocation strategy imply intent to share the physical
                    infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among all members
                    of this group.
      - ISOLATION: Isolation strategy imply intent to not share the physical
                   infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among the members
                   of this group.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:placement-groups

  Leaves

    name: name, type: STRING

    name: value-decimal, type: DECIMAL64, description: Current value for a decimal parameter

    name: units, type: STRING, description: Measured Counter Units (e.g., Packets, Kbps, Mbps, etc.)
    name: aggregation-type, type: ENUM
    name: method, type: ENUM, description: How to compare each sample with the threshold to determine if
    the threshold has been crossed.
    name: entity-type, type: STRING, description: Entity type
    name: id-generator-fn, type: STRING, description: Javascript function specifying how to transform the input fields into a unique ID that can be mapped to a Managed Object
    name: collection-period, type: UINT32, description: Collection period in seconds
    name: snmp-community, type: STRING, description: SNMP community
    name: snmp-version, type: STRING, description: SNMP version
    name: snmp-operation, type: ENUM, description: SNMP operation
    name: kafka-brokers, type: STRING, description: A comma-separated list of known Kafka Brokers in the format <host>:<port>
    name: kafka-topic, type: STRING, description: Name of Kafka topic to read from.
    name: kafka-scheme, type: STRING, description: Name of Kafka schema to use for this particular topic.

2.1.1.3.3.1.18  list rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Policy ID
    name: operator, type: ENUM, description: How to compare each sample with the threshold to determine if
    the threshold has been crossed.
    name: hold-on-for-n-samples, type: UINT32, description: The number of samples for which the condition (sample value <operator>
    threshold) is met in order to raise an alarm or upgrade the severity
    of the Threshold Crossing Alarm.
    name: hold-off-for-n-samples, type: UINT32, description: The number of samples for which the condition ( sample value
    <operator> threshold) is NOT be met in order to clear an alarm
    or downgrade the severity of the Threshold Crossing Alarm.
    name: monitoring-param-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Reference to monitoring parameter monitored by this policy

2.1.1.3.3.1.18.1  list rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold
  Description
    When enough sample values are found to be above/below(depending
    on defined operator) the defined threshold a Threshold Crossing
    Alert(TCA) alarm is generated. When enough samples are found to
    be crossing the threshold in the reverse direction will either
    clear the alarm or downgrade its severity
  Leaves
    name: severity, type: ENUM, description: The severity of the alarm generated when the threshold is crossed.
    If using operator=GT, threshold values must comply with this constraint:
    minor < major < critical. If using operator=LT, threshold values
    must comply with this constraint: minor > major > critical.
    name: value, type: DECIMAL64, description: Threshold value
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold[rwmanoprojectnsd:severity='MINOR']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-project-nsd:nsd-catalog/nsd/STRING/tca-policy/STRING/threshold/MINOR
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    C,/rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold

    C,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy[rwmanoprojectnsd:id='STRING']/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold[rwmanoprojectnsd:severity='MINOR']

2.1.1.3.3.1.18.1.1  list rwmanoprojectnsd:action
  Description
    Actions to take when the threshold is crossed.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of action
    name: threshold-adjustment, type: DECIMAL64, description: Amount by which all thresholds defined are to be adjusted when
    this action is taken. Typical use case is for scale-in/scale-out.
    If scale-out is based on number of sessions, the first scale-out
    occurs at a certain threshold but the second scale-out will occur
    at a much higher session count than the first since now more resources
    are allocated allowing for more sessions.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd-catalog/rwmanoprojectnsd:nsd/rwmanoprojectnsd:tca-policy/rwmanoprojectnsd:threshold/rwmanoprojectnsd:action
  XPath Keyed Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.4  list rwmanovnfr:external-vlr
  Leaves
    name: id, type: LEAFREF, description: Id of this VL, this is a reference to the VLR id in the project's
    vlr-catalog
    name: name, type: STRING, description: VLR name.
    name: nsr-id-ref, type: STRING, description: NS instance identifier.
    This is a leafref /rwmanoproject:project/internal/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr/nsr:id
    name: vld-ref, type: STRING, description: Reference to VLD
    /rwmanoproject:project/internal/nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr[nsr:id=../nsr-id-ref]
    /nsd/vld:vld/vld:id
    name: res-id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for resmgr id mapping
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: vendor, type: STRING, description: Provider of the VLR.
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description of the VLR.
    name: version, type: STRING, description: Version of the VLR
    name: type, type: ENUM
    name: root-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the aggregate bandwidth.
    name: leaf-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the bandwidth of branches.
    name: create-time, type: UINT32, description: Creation timestamp of this Virtual Link.
    The timestamp is expressed as seconds
    since unix epoch - 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z
    name: mgmt-network, type: BOOLEAN, description: Is this a management network?
    name: network-id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the allocated network resource.
    name: vim-network-name, type: STRING, description: Name of network in VIM account. This is used to indicate
    pre-provisioned network name in cloud account.
    name: status, type: ENUM, description: Status of the virtual link record.
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of the Virtual Link
    init                 : The VL is in init stat.
    vl-alloc-pending     : The VL alloc is pending in VIM
    running              : The VL is up  and running in VM
    vl-terminate-pending : The VL is being terminated in VIM.
    terminated           : The VL is terminated in the VM.
    failed               : The VL instantiation failed in VIM.

    name: datacenter, type: STRING, description: Datacenter name to use when instantiating
    the network service.
    name: network-pool, type: STRING, description: The network pool the resource was allocated from.
    name: ipv4-nat-pool-name, type: STRING, description: IPV4 nat pool name

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.5  list rwmanovnfr:placement-groups-info
  Description

      Placement groups to which this VDU belongs and its
      cloud construct
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Place group construct to define the compute resource placement strategy
    in cloud environment
    name: requirement, type: STRING, description: This is free text space used to describe the intent/rationale
    behind this placement group. This is for human consumption only
    name: strategy, type: ENUM, description: Strategy associated with this placement group
    Following values are possible
      - COLOCATION: Colocation strategy imply intent to share the physical
                    infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among all members
                    of this group.
      - ISOLATION: Isolation strategy imply intent to not share the physical
                   infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among the members
                   of this group.

    name: cloud-type, type: ENUM
    name: aws-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: openmano-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: mock-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: cloudsim-construct, type: EMPTY
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.2.1  list rwmanovnfr:rule
  Description
    List of rules needed for security groups
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Name/id of the rule
    name: direction, type: ENUM, description: Direction of traffic w.r.t VDU
    name: ethertype, type: ENUM, description: IPv4 or IPv6
    name: ip-protocol, type: UINT8, description: IP protocol, 0-255
    name: ip-protocol-string, type: ENUM, description: IP protocol string, within the following values
    any or 0, ah or 51, dccp or 33, egp or 8, esp or 50, gre or 47, icmp or 1, icmpv6 or 58,
    igmp or 2, ipip or 4, ipv6-encap or 41, ipv6-frag or 44, ipv6-icmp or 58, ipv6-nonxt or 59,
    ipv6-opts or 60, ipv6-route or 43, ospf or 89, pgm or 113, rsvp or 46, sctp or 132, tcp or 6,
    udp or 17, udplite or 136, vrrp or 112. 
    name: port-range-min, type: UINT16, description: Minimum port number in the range 0-65535
    name: port-range-max, type: UINT16, description: Maximum port number in the range 0-65535
    name: cidr, type: UNION, description: Known CIDR
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.3.1  list rwmanovnfr:config-parameter-source
  Description
    The list of parameters exposed by this VNF
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the source
    name: description, type: STRING, description:  Description of the source
    name: descriptor, type: STRING, description: Location of this source as an xpath.
    For example:
    ../../../mgmt-interface/port
    name: attribute, type: STRING, description: Location of this source as runtime attribute.
    The value is <xpath>, <attribute_name>
    For example:
    ../../../mgmt-interface, ip-address
    which retruns the ip-address assigned to the
    mgmt-interface after VNF instantiation.
    name: config-primitive-name-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: A leafref to configuration primitive.
    This refers to a config parameter whose
    output parameter is referred in out-parameter.
    name: parameter-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Name of the output parameter in the config primitiive
    name: value, type: STRING, description: Pre-defined value to be used for this source
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.5  list rwmanovnfr:internal-vld
  Description
    List of Internal Virtual Link Descriptors (VLD).
    The internal VLD describes the basic topology of
    the connectivity such as E-LAN, E-Line, E-Tree.
    between internal VNF components of the system.
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the VLD
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the internal VLD
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: description, type: STRING
    name: type, type: ENUM
    name: resource-name, type: STRING, description: Internal VL name in VIM
    name: root-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the aggregate bandwidth.
    name: leaf-bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: For ELAN this is the bandwidth of branches.
    name: vim-network-name, type: STRING, description: Name of network in VIM account. This is used to indicate
    pre-provisioned network name in cloud account.
    name: ip-profile-ref, type: STRING, description: Named reference to IP-profile object
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:internal-vld

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.7  list rwmanovnfr:connection-point
  Description
    List for external connection points. Each VNF has one
    or more external connection points that connect the VNF
    to other VNFs or to external networks. Each VNF exposes
    connection points to the orchestrator, which can construct
    network services by connecting the connection points
    between different VNFs. The NFVO will use VLDs and VNFFGs
    at the network service level to construct network services.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the connection point
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the internal connection points
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
    name: port-security-enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Enables the port security for the port
    name: vlr-ref, type: STRING, description: Reference to VLR id
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:connection-point

    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:connection-point[rwmanovnfr:name='STRING']

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.8  list rwmanovnfr:vdu
  Description
    List of Virtual Deployment Units
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Unique id for the VDU
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Unique name for the VDU
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description of the VDU.
    name: count, type: UINT64, description: Number of instances of VDU
    name: resource-name, type: STRING, description: VDU name in VIM
    name: mgmt-vpci, type: STRING, description: Specifies the virtual PCI address. Expressed in
    the following format dddd:dd:dd.d. For example
    0000:00:12.0. This information can be used to
    pass as metadata during the VM creation.
    name: vm-flavor-name, type: STRING, description: flavor name to be used while creating vm using cloud account
    name: image, type: STRING, description: Image name for the software image.
    If the image name is found within the VNF package it will
    be uploaded to all VIM accounts during onboarding process.
    Otherwise, the image must be added to the VIM account with
    the same name as entered here.

    name: image-checksum, type: STRING, description: Image md5sum for the software image.
    The md5sum, if provided, along with the image name uniquely
    identifies an image uploaded to the CAL.

    name: cloud-init, type: STRING, description: Contents of cloud-init script, provided inline, in cloud-config format
    name: cloud-init-file, type: STRING, description: Name of file with contents of cloud-init script in cloud-config format
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.8.2  container rwmanovnfr:guest-epa
  Leaves
    name: trusted-execution, type: BOOLEAN, description: This VM should be allocated from trusted pool
    name: mempage-size, type: ENUM, description: Memory page allocation size. If a VM requires
    hugepages, it should choose LARGE or SIZE_2MB
    or SIZE_1GB. If the VM prefers hugepages it
    should choose PREFER_LARGE.
    LARGE        : Require hugepages (either 2MB or 1GB)
    SMALL        : Doesn't require hugepages
    SIZE_2MB     : Requires 2MB hugepages
    SIZE_1GB     : Requires 1GB hugepages
    PREFER_LARGE : Application prefers hugepages
    name: cpu-pinning-policy, type: ENUM, description: CPU pinning policy describes association
    between virtual CPUs in guest and the
    physical CPUs in the host.
    DEDICATED : Virtual CPUs are pinned to
      physical CPUs
    SHARED    : Multiple VMs may share the
      same physical CPUs.
    ANY       : Any policy is acceptable for the VM
    name: cpu-thread-pinning-policy, type: ENUM, description: CPU thread pinning policy describes how to
    place the guest CPUs when the host supports
    hyper threads:
    AVOID   : Avoids placing a guest on a host
    with threads.
    SEPARATE: Places vCPUs on separate cores,
    and avoids placing two vCPUs on
    two threads of same core.
    ISOLATE : Places each vCPU on a different core,
    and places no vCPUs from a different
    guest on the same core.
    PREFER  : Attempts to place vCPUs on threads
    of the same core.
    name: numa-unaware, type: EMPTY
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:vdu/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:vdu[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr/STRING/input/vnfd/vdu/STRING/guest-epa
  RW Keyspec XPath Path

  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.8.2.2  container rwmanovnfr:numa-node-policy
  Description
    This policy defines NUMA topology of the
    guest. Specifically identifies if the guest
    should be run on a host with one NUMA
    node or multiple NUMA nodes. As an example
    a guest might need 8 VCPUs and 4 GB of
    memory. However, it might need the VCPUs
    and memory distributed across multiple
    NUMA nodes. In this scenario, NUMA node
    1 could run with 6 VCPUs and 3GB, and
    NUMA node 2 could run with 2 VCPUs and
    1GB.
  Leaves
    name: node-cnt, type: UINT16, description: The number of NUMA nodes to expose to the VM.
    name: mem-policy, type: ENUM, description: This policy specifies how the memory should
    be allocated in a multi-node scenario.
    STRICT    : The memory must be allocated
    strictly from the memory attached
    to the NUMA node.
    PREFERRED : The memory should be allocated
    preferentially from the memory
    attached to the NUMA node
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:vdu/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa/rwmanovnfr:numa-node-policy
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:vdu[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa/rwmanovnfr:numa-node-policy
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr/STRING/input/vnfd/vdu/STRING/guest-epa/numa-node-policy
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    D,/rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:vdu/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa/rwmanovnfr:numa-node-policy
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    D,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:vdu[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa/rwmanovnfr:numa-node-policy

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.8.6  list rwmanovnfr:alarm
  Leaves
    name: alarm-id, type: STRING, description: This field is reserved for the identifier assigned by the VIM provider
    name: name, type: STRING, description: A human readable string to identify the alarm
    name: description, type: STRING, description: A description of this alarm
    name: vdur-id, type: STRING, description: The identifier of the VDUR that the alarm is associated with
    name: repeat, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates whether the alarm should be repeatedly emitted
    while the associated threshold has been crossed.
    name: enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates whether the alarm has been enabled or
    disabled.
    name: severity, type: ENUM, description: A measure of the importance or urgency of the alarm
    name: metric, type: ENUM, description: The metric to be tracked by this alarm.
    name: statistic, type: ENUM, description: The type of metric statistic that is tracked by this alarm
    name: operation, type: ENUM, description: The relational operator used to define whether an alarm should be
    triggered in certain scenarios, such as if the metric statistic
    goes above or below a specified value.
    name: value, type: DECIMAL64, description: This value defines the threshold that, if crossed, will trigger
    the alarm.
    name: period, type: UINT32, description: The period defines the length of time (seconds) that the metric
    data are collected over in oreder to evaluate the chosen
    statistic.
    name: evaluations, type: UINT32, description: Defines the length of time (seconds) in which metric data are
    collected in order to evaluate the chosen statistic.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:vdu/rwmanovnfr:alarm

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.8.8  list rwmanovnfr:internal-connection-point
  Description
    List for internal connection points. Each VNFC
    has zero or more internal connection points.
    Internal connection points are used for connecting
    the VNF with components internal to the VNF. If a VNF
    has only one VNFC, it may not have any internal
    connection points.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the connection point
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the internal connection points
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
    name: port-security-enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Enables the port security for the port
    name: vlr-ref, type: STRING, description: Reference to VLR id
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:vdu/rwmanovnfr:internal-connection-point

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.8.9  list rwmanovnfr:interface
  Description
    List of Interfaces (external and internal) for the VNF
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the interface. Note that this
    name has only local significance to the VDU.
    name: position, type: UINT32, description: Explicit Position of the interface within the list
    name: resource-name, type: STRING, description: Interface name in VIM
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the Interface
    name: internal-connection-point-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Leaf Ref to the particular internal connection point
    name: external-connection-point-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Leaf Ref to the particular external connection point
    name: vim-port-name, type: STRING, description: Pre-created port in the corresponding subnet/network
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:vdu/rwmanovnfr:interface

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.8.9.2  container rwmanovnfr:virtual-interface
  Description
    Container for the virtual interface properties
  Leaves
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Specifies the type of virtual interface
    between VM and host.
    VIRTIO          : Use the traditional VIRTIO interface.
    PCI-PASSTHROUGH : Use PCI-PASSTHROUGH interface.
    SR-IOV          : Use SR-IOV interface.
    SRIOV-DIRECT-PHYSICAL: Use SR-IOV interface with direct-physical.
    E1000           : Emulate E1000 interface.
    RTL8139         : Emulate RTL8139 interface.
    PCNET           : Emulate PCNET interface.
    AVP             : Windriver Accelerated Virtual port
    OM-MGMT         : Used to specify openmano mgmt external-connection type
    name: vpci, type: STRING, description: Specifies the virtual PCI address. Expressed in
    the following format dddd:dd:dd.d. For example
    0000:00:12.0. This information can be used to
    pass as metadata during the VM creation.
    name: bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: Aggregate bandwidth of the NIC.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:vdu/rwmanovnfr:interface/rwmanovnfr:virtual-interface
