2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.8.10  list rwmanovnfr:volumes
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name for the volume configuration
    name: device-name, type: STRING, description: Device-name of the disk eg. vda, vdb etc
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description for Volume
    name: size, type: UINT64, description: Size of disk in GB
    name: ephemeral, type: EMPTY
    name: image, type: STRING, description: Image name for the software image.
    If the image name is found within the VNF package it will
    be uploaded to all VIM accounts during onboarding process.
    Otherwise, the image must be added to the VIM account with
    the same name as entered here.

    name: image-checksum, type: STRING, description: Image md5sum for the software image.
    The md5sum, if provided, along with the image name uniquely
    identifies an image uploaded to the CAL.

    name: volume-ref, type: STRING, description: A reference to or the name of a pre-existing volume in the VIM
    name: boot-volume, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates if this is boot volume or not
    name: boot-priority, type: INT32, description: Boot priority associated with volume
    name: device-bus, type: ENUM, description: Type of disk-bus on which this disk is exposed to guest
    name: device-type, type: ENUM, description: The type of device as exposed to guest
    name: volume-type, type: STRING, description: Type of the volume

    name: password, type: STRING, description: The HTTP basic auth password

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.12  list rwmanovnfr:placement-groups
  Description
    List of placement groups at VNF level
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Place group construct to define the compute resource placement strategy
    in cloud environment
    name: requirement, type: STRING, description: This is free text space used to describe the intent/rationale
    behind this placement group. This is for human consumption only
    name: strategy, type: ENUM, description: Strategy associated with this placement group
    Following values are possible
      - COLOCATION: Colocation strategy imply intent to share the physical
                    infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among all members
                    of this group.
      - ISOLATION: Isolation strategy imply intent to not share the physical
                   infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among the members
                   of this group.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:placement-groups

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.13  list rwmanovnfr:tca-policy
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Policy ID
    name: operator, type: ENUM, description: How to compare each sample with the threshold to determine if
    the threshold has been crossed.
    name: hold-on-for-n-samples, type: UINT32, description: The number of samples for which the condition (sample value <operator>
    threshold) is met in order to raise an alarm or upgrade the severity
    of the Threshold Crossing Alarm.
    name: hold-off-for-n-samples, type: UINT32, description: The number of samples for which the condition ( sample value
    <operator> threshold) is NOT be met in order to clear an alarm
    or downgrade the severity of the Threshold Crossing Alarm.
    name: monitoring-param-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Reference to monitoring parameter monitored by this condition
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:tca-policy

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.13.1  list rwmanovnfr:threshold
  Description
    When enough sample values are found to be above/below(depending
    on defined operator) the defined threshold a Threshold Crossing
    Alert(TCA) alarm is generated. When enough samples are found to
    be crossing the threshold in the reverse direction will either
    clear the alarm or downgrade its severity
  Leaves
    name: severity, type: ENUM, description: The severity of the alarm generated when the threshold is crossed.
    If using operator=GT, threshold values must comply with this constraint:
    minor < major < critical. If using operator=LT, threshold values
    must comply with this constraint: minor > major > critical.
    name: value, type: DECIMAL64, description: Threshold value
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:tca-policy/rwmanovnfr:threshold
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:tca-policy[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:threshold[rwmanovnfr:severity='MINOR']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr/STRING/input/vnfd/tca-policy/STRING/threshold/MINOR
  RW Keyspec XPath Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.3.7.13.1.1  list rwmanovnfr:action
  Description
    Actions to take when the threshold is crossed.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of action
    name: threshold-adjustment, type: DECIMAL64, description: Amount by which all thresholds defined are to be adjusted when
    this action is taken. Typical use case is for scale-in/scale-out.
    If scale-out is based on number of sessions, the first scale-out
    occurs at a certain threshold but the second scale-out will occur
    at a much higher session count than the first since now more resources
    are allocated allowing for more sessions.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:input/rwmanovnfr:vnfd/rwmanovnfr:tca-policy/rwmanovnfr:threshold/rwmanovnfr:action

2.1.1.3.4.1.4  container rwmanovnfr:oper-state
  Description
    This is the operational state during VNF lifecycle mgmt in the VNFM 2.0
    tasklet.
  Leaves
    name: nsr-id-ref, type: STRING, description: NS instance identifier.
    This is a leafref /nsr:ns-instance-config/nsr:nsr/nsr:id
    name: member-vnf-index-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Reference to member VNF index in Network service.
    name: dashboard-url, type: STRING, description: Dashboard URL
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: VNFR short name.
    name: vendor, type: STRING, description: Vendor of the VNFR.
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description of the VNFR.
    name: version, type: STRING, description: Version of the VNFR
    name: create-time, type: UINT32, description: Creation timestamp of this Virtual Network
    Function.  The timestamp is expressed as
    seconds since unix epoch - 1970-01-01T00:00:00Z
    name: datacenter, type: STRING, description: Datacenter name to use when instantiating
    the VNF.
    name: vnfm-account-name, type: STRING, description: Name of SVNFM account used for VNF instantiation
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of the VNFR instance
    pre-init            : The VNF before Input Param substitution
    init                : The VNF has just started.
    vl-init-phase       : The internal VLs in the VNF are being instantiated.
    vm-init-phase       : The VMs for VDUs in the VNF are being instantiated.
    running             : The VNF is in running state.
    terminate           : The VNF is being terminated.
    vm-terminate-phase  : The VMs in the VNF are being terminated.
    vl-terminate-phase  : The internal VLs in the VNF are being terminated.
    terminated          : The VNF is in the terminated state.
    secgrp-init-phase   : The security groups in the VNF are being instantiated.
    secgrp-terminate-phase    : The security groups in the VNF are being terminated.
    failed              : The VNF instantiation failed

    name: operational-status-details, type: STRING, description: The error message in case of a failed VNFR operational status
    name: config-status, type: ENUM, description: The configuration status of the NS instance
    configuring: At least one of the VNFs in this instance is in configuring state
    configured:  All the VNFs in this NS instance are configured or config-not-needed state
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:oper-state
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:oper-state
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr/STRING/oper-state

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.3  list rwmanovnfr:security-group
  Description
    List of VNF security groups
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the security-group
    name: description, type: STRING, description:  Description of the source
    name: resource-name, type: STRING, description: security group name in VIM
    name: security-group-desc-ref, type: STRING, description: Security group name in VNFD
    name: vim-security-group-id, type: STRING, description: Security group identifier in VIM
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of this security group
    init                : The sec-group has just started.
    secgrp-init-phase       : The sec-group in the VNF is being created in VIM.
    secgrp-alloc-pending    : The  sec-group alloc is pending in VIM
    running             : The sec-group is active in VM
    secgrp-terminate-phase  : The sec-group in the VNF is being terminated in VIM.
    terminated          : The sec-group is in the terminated state.
    failed              : The sec-grp instantiation failed.

    name: operational-status-details, type: STRING, description: The error message in case of a failed security group operational status
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.6  list rwmanovnfr:connection-point
  Description
    List for external connection points. Each VNF has one
    or more external connection points. As the name
    implies that external connection points are used for
    connecting the VNF to other VNFs or to external networks.
    Each VNF exposes these connection points to the
    orchestrator. The orchestrator can construct network
    services by connecting the connection points between
    different VNFs. The NFVO will use VLDs and VNFFGs at
    the network service level to construct network services.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the connection point
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the internal connection points
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
    name: port-security-enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Enables the port security for the port
    name: vlr-ref, type: STRING, description: Reference to VLR id
    name: vlr-id-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Reference to the VLR associated with this connection point
    name: mac-address, type: STRING, description: MAC address assigned to the internal connection point
    name: connection-point-id, type: STRING, description: The id assigned to this connection point by VIM
    name: vim-cp-name, type: STRING, description: Connection point name in VIM
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of this connection point        init                : The connection-point has just started.        cp-init-phase       : The connection-point in the VNF is being created in VIM.        cp-alloc-pending    : The connection-point alloc is pending in VIM        inactive            : Connection-point setup in VIM but not attached to VM        active              : The connection-point is active in VM        cp-terminate-phase  : The connection-point in the VNF is being terminated in VIM.        terminated          : The connection-point is in the terminated state.        failed              : The connection-point instantiation failed.      
    name: operational-status-details, type: STRING, description: The error message in case of a failed connection point operational status
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.7  list rwmanovnfr:vdur
  Description
    List of Virtual Deployment Units
  Leaves
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Unique id for the VDU
    name: name, type: STRING, description: name of the instantiated VDUR
    name: unique-short-name, type: STRING, description: Short Unique name of the VDU
    This will be of the format NSR name-ShortnedString-VDUname
    NSR name and VDU name shall be constrained to 10 characters
    name: vdu-id-ref, type: LEAFREF
    name: vim-id, type: STRING, description: Allocated VM resource id
    name: flavor-id, type: STRING, description: VIM assigned flavor id
    name: image-id, type: STRING, description: VIM assigned image id
    name: management-ip, type: UNION, description: Management IP address
    name: vm-management-ip, type: UNION, description: VM Private Management IP address
    name: console-url, type: STRING, description: Console URL for this VDU, if available
    name: preexisting-resource-name, type: STRING, description: Name of the preexisting virtual machine in the vim
    name: delete-on-terminate, type: BOOLEAN, description: Controls the deletion of preexisting virtal machine in vim
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of the VDU
    init                : The VDU has just started.
    cp-init-phase       : The connection points in the VDU are being created in VIM.
    volume-init-phase   : The volumes in the VDU are being created in VIM.
    vm-init-phase       : The VMs in the VNF are being created in VIM.
    running             : The VDU is active in VIM
    vm-terminate-phase  : The VMs in the VDU are being terminated in VIM.
    volume-terminate-phase  : The volumes in the VDU are being terminated in VIM.
    cp-terminate-phase  : The connection points in the VDU are being terminated in VIM.
    terminated          : The VDU is in the terminated state.
    failed              : The VDU instantiation failed.

    name: operational-status-details, type: STRING, description: The error message in case of a failed VDUR operational status
  XPath Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.7.2  container rwmanovnfr:guest-epa
  Leaves
    name: trusted-execution, type: BOOLEAN, description: This VM should be allocated from trusted pool
    name: mempage-size, type: ENUM, description: Memory page allocation size. If a VM requires
    hugepages, it should choose LARGE or SIZE_2MB
    or SIZE_1GB. If the VM prefers hugepages it
    should choose PREFER_LARGE.
    LARGE        : Require hugepages (either 2MB or 1GB)
    SMALL        : Doesn't require hugepages
    SIZE_2MB     : Requires 2MB hugepages
    SIZE_1GB     : Requires 1GB hugepages
    PREFER_LARGE : Application prefers hugepages
    name: cpu-pinning-policy, type: ENUM, description: CPU pinning policy describes association
    between virtual CPUs in guest and the
    physical CPUs in the host.
    DEDICATED : Virtual CPUs are pinned to
      physical CPUs
    SHARED    : Multiple VMs may share the
      same physical CPUs.
    ANY       : Any policy is acceptable for the VM
    name: cpu-thread-pinning-policy, type: ENUM, description: CPU thread pinning policy describes how to
    place the guest CPUs when the host supports
    hyper threads:
    AVOID   : Avoids placing a guest on a host
    with threads.
    SEPARATE: Places vCPUs on separate cores,
    and avoids placing two vCPUs on
    two threads of same core.
    ISOLATE : Places each vCPU on a different core,
    and places no vCPUs from a different
    guest on the same core.
    PREFER  : Attempts to place vCPUs on threads
    of the same core.
    name: numa-unaware, type: EMPTY
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.7.2.2  container rwmanovnfr:numa-node-policy
  Description
    This policy defines NUMA topology of the
    guest. Specifically identifies if the guest
    should be run on a host with one NUMA
    node or multiple NUMA nodes. As an example
    a guest might need 8 VCPUs and 4 GB of
    memory. However, it might need the VCPUs
    and memory distributed across multiple
    NUMA nodes. In this scenario, NUMA node
    1 could run with 6 VCPUs and 3GB, and
    NUMA node 2 could run with 2 VCPUs and
    1GB.
  Leaves
    name: node-cnt, type: UINT16, description: The number of NUMA nodes to expose to the VM.
    name: mem-policy, type: ENUM, description: This policy specifies how the memory should
    be allocated in a multi-node scenario.
    STRICT    : The memory must be allocated
    strictly from the memory attached
    to the NUMA node.
    PREFERRED : The memory should be allocated
    preferentially from the memory
    attached to the NUMA node
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa/rwmanovnfr:numa-node-policy
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa/rwmanovnfr:numa-node-policy
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr/STRING/oper-state/vdur/STRING/guest-epa/numa-node-policy
  RW Keyspec XPath Path
    D,/rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa/rwmanovnfr:numa-node-policy
  RW Keyspec XPath Keyed Path
    D,/rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:guest-epa/rwmanovnfr:numa-node-policy

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.7.7  list rwmanovnfr:volumes
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name for the volume configuration
    name: device-name, type: STRING, description: Device-name of the disk eg. vda, vdb etc
    name: volume-id, type: STRING, description: VIM assigned volume id
    name: vim-volume-name, type: STRING, description: Volume name in VIM
    name: preexisting-resource-name, type: STRING, description: Name of the preexisting volumes in the vim
    name: delete-on-terminate, type: BOOLEAN, description: Controls the deletion of preexisting volumes in vim
    name: description, type: STRING, description: Description for Volume
    name: size, type: UINT64, description: Size of disk in GB
    name: ephemeral, type: EMPTY
    name: image, type: STRING, description: Image name for the software image.
    If the image name is found within the VNF package it will
    be uploaded to all VIM accounts during onboarding process.
    Otherwise, the image must be added to the VIM account with
    the same name as entered here.

    name: image-checksum, type: STRING, description: Image md5sum for the software image.
    The md5sum, if provided, along with the image name uniquely
    identifies an image uploaded to the CAL.

    name: volume-ref, type: STRING, description: A reference to or the name of a pre-existing volume in the VIM
    name: boot-volume, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates if this is boot volume or not
    name: boot-priority, type: INT32, description: Boot priority associated with volume
    name: device-bus, type: ENUM, description: Type of disk-bus on which this disk is exposed to guest
    name: device-type, type: ENUM, description: The type of device as exposed to guest
    name: volume-type, type: STRING, description: Type of the volume
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of this connection point
    init                : The volume has just started.
    inactive            : Volume setup in VIM but not attached to VM
    vol-init-phase      : Volume creation initialization
    running             : The volume is active in VM
    vol-terminate-phase  : The volume in the VNF is being terminated in VIM.
    terminated          : The volume is in the terminated state.
    failed              : The volume instantiation failed.

    name: operational-status-details, type: STRING, description: The error message in case of a failed volume operational status
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur/rwmanovnfr:volumes

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.7.8  list rwmanovnfr:alarms
  Description
    A list of the alarms that have been created for this VDU
  Leaves
    name: alarm-id, type: STRING, description: This field is reserved for the identifier assigned by the VIM provider
    name: name, type: STRING, description: A human readable string to identify the alarm
    name: description, type: STRING, description: A description of this alarm
    name: vdur-id, type: STRING, description: The identifier of the VDUR that the alarm is associated with
    name: repeat, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates whether the alarm should be repeatedly emitted
    while the associated threshold has been crossed.
    name: enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: This flag indicates whether the alarm has been enabled or
    disabled.
    name: severity, type: ENUM, description: A measure of the importance or urgency of the alarm
    name: metric, type: ENUM, description: The metric to be tracked by this alarm.
    name: statistic, type: ENUM, description: The type of metric statistic that is tracked by this alarm
    name: operation, type: ENUM, description: The relational operator used to define whether an alarm should be
    triggered in certain scenarios, such as if the metric statistic
    goes above or below a specified value.
    name: value, type: DECIMAL64, description: This value defines the threshold that, if crossed, will trigger
    the alarm.
    name: period, type: UINT32, description: The period defines the length of time (seconds) that the metric
    data are collected over in oreder to evaluate the chosen
    statistic.
    name: evaluations, type: UINT32, description: Defines the length of time (seconds) in which metric data are
    collected in order to evaluate the chosen statistic.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur/rwmanovnfr:alarms

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.7.9  list rwmanovnfr:internal-connection-point
  Description
    List for internal connection points. Each VNFC
    has zero or more internal connection points.
    Internal connection points are used for connecting
    the VNF components internal to the VNF. If a VNF
    has only one VNFC, it may not have any internal
    connection points.
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of the connection point
    name: id, type: STRING, description: Identifier for the internal connection points
    name: short-name, type: STRING, description: Short name to appear as label in the UI
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the connection point.
    name: port-security-enabled, type: BOOLEAN, description: Enables the port security for the port
    name: vlr-ref, type: STRING, description: Reference to VLR id
    name: mac-address, type: STRING, description: MAC address assigned to the internal connection point
    name: connection-point-id, type: STRING, description: The id assigned to this connection point by VIM
    name: vim-cp-name, type: STRING, description: Connection point name in VIM
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of this connection point        init                : The connection-point has just started.        cp-init-phase       : The connection-point in the VNF is being created in VIM.        cp-alloc-pending    : The connection-point alloc is pending in VIM        inactive            : Connection-point setup in VIM but not attached to VM        active              : The connection-point is active in VM        cp-terminate-phase  : The connection-point in the VNF is being terminated in VIM.        terminated          : The connection-point is in the terminated state.        failed              : The connection-point instantiation failed.      
    name: operational-status-details, type: STRING, description: The error message in case of a failed connection point operational status
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur/rwmanovnfr:internal-connection-point
  XPath Keyed Path
    /rw-project:project[rw-project:name='STRING']/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']/rwmanovnfr:internal-connection-point[rwmanovnfr:id='STRING']
  RW.REST URI Path
    /rw-project:project/STRING/rwmano-project:internal/rwmano-vnfr:vnfr-catalog/vnfr/STRING/oper-state/vdur/STRING/internal-connection-point/STRING

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.7.10  list rwmanovnfr:interface
  Description
    List of internal interfaces (internal and external) for the VNF
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Name of interface. Note that this
    name has only local significance to the VDU.
    name: position, type: UINT32, description: Explicit position of the interface within the list
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Type of the Interface
    name: preexisting-resource-name, type: STRING, description: Name of the preexisting volumes in the vim
    name: delete-on-terminate, type: BOOLEAN, description: Controls the deletion of preexisting volumes in vim
    name: internal-connection-point-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Leaf Ref to the particular internal connection point
    name: external-connection-point-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Leaf Ref to the particular external connection point
    name: vlr-id-ref, type: LEAFREF, description: Reference to the VLR associated with this interface
    name: mac-address, type: STRING, description: MAC address assigned to the interface
    name: interface-id, type: STRING, description: Interface ID in VIM
    name: vim-intf-name, type: STRING, description: Interface name in VIM
    name: operational-status, type: ENUM, description: The operational status of this connection point
    init                : The connection-point has just started.
    cp-init-phase       : The connection-point in the VNF is being created in VIM.
    cp-alloc-pending    : The connection-point alloc is pending in VIM
    inactive            : Connection-point setup in VIM but not attached to VM
    running             : The connection-point is active in VM
    cp-terminate-phase  : The connection-point in the VNF is being terminated in VIM.
    terminated          : The connection-point is in the terminated state.
    failed              : The connection-point instantiation failed.

    name: operational-status-details, type: STRING, description: The error message in case of a failed connection point operational status
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur/rwmanovnfr:interface
  XPath Keyed Path

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.7.10.1  container rwmanovnfr:virtual-interface
  Description
    Container for the virtual interface properties
  Leaves
    name: type, type: ENUM, description: Specifies the type of virtual interface
    between VM and host.
    VIRTIO          : Use the traditional VIRTIO interface.
    PCI-PASSTHROUGH : Use PCI-PASSTHROUGH interface.
    SR-IOV          : Use SR-IOV interface.
    name: bandwidth, type: UINT64, description: Aggregate bandwidth of the NIC.
    name: ovs-offload, type: ENUM, description: Defines if the NIC supports OVS offload.
    MANDATORY : OVS offload support in the NIC is mandatory.
    PREFERRED : OVS offload support in the NIC is preferred.
    name: vendor-id, type: STRING, description: Specifies the vendor specific id for
    the device. This is used when a NIC from
    specific HW vendor is required.
    name: datapath-library, type: STRING, description: Specifies the name and version of the datapath
    library the NIC is expected to support.
    name: provider-network-name, type: STRING, description: Name of the provider network to which this
    NIC is attached.
  XPath Path
    /rw-project:project/rwmanoproject:internal/rwmanovnfr:vnfr-catalog/rwmanovnfr:vnfr/rwmanovnfr:oper-state/rwmanovnfr:vdur/rwmanovnfr:interface/rwmanovnfr:virtual-interface

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.7.10.2  list rwmanovnfr:address-data
  Leaves

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.7.11  list rwmanovnfr:placement-groups-info
  Description

      Placement groups to which this VDU belongs and its
      cloud construct
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Place group construct to define the compute resource placement strategy
    in cloud environment
    name: requirement, type: STRING, description: This is free text space used to describe the intent/rationale
    behind this placement group. This is for human consumption only
    name: strategy, type: ENUM, description: Strategy associated with this placement group
    Following values are possible
      - COLOCATION: Colocation strategy imply intent to share the physical
                    infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among all members
                    of this group.
      - ISOLATION: Isolation strategy imply intent to not share the physical
                   infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among the members
                   of this group.

    name: cloud-type, type: ENUM
    name: aws-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: openmano-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: mock-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: cloudsim-construct, type: EMPTY

2.1.1.3.4.1.4.10  list rwmanovnfr:placement-groups-info
  Description

      Placement groups to which this VDU belongs and its
      cloud construct
  Leaves
    name: name, type: STRING, description: Place group construct to define the compute resource placement strategy
    in cloud environment
    name: requirement, type: STRING, description: This is free text space used to describe the intent/rationale
    behind this placement group. This is for human consumption only
    name: strategy, type: ENUM, description: Strategy associated with this placement group
    Following values are possible
      - COLOCATION: Colocation strategy imply intent to share the physical
                    infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among all members
                    of this group.
      - ISOLATION: Isolation strategy imply intent to not share the physical
                   infrastructure (hypervisor/network) among the members
                   of this group.

    name: cloud-type, type: ENUM
    name: aws-construct, type: EMPTY
    name: openmano-construct, type: EMPTY
